1
00:00:10,360 --> 00:00:12,560
<i>Paradorn.</i>

2
00:00:12,640 --> 00:00:14,840
<i>Paradorn.</i>

3
00:00:14,920 --> 00:00:16,880
<i>Paradorn.</i>

4
00:00:18,480 --> 00:00:22,520
<i>They say power changes people.</i>

5
00:00:23,280 --> 00:00:26,920
<i>Or maybe it simply rips off the mask</i>

6
00:00:27,000 --> 00:00:28,720
<i>and reveals</i>

7
00:00:29,480 --> 00:00:31,440
<i>who they really are.</i>

8
00:01:35,200 --> 00:01:38,680
1 MONTH BEFORE THE ELECTION

9
00:01:41,680 --> 00:01:43,800
Has anyone ever wondered, like I have,

10
00:01:44,560 --> 00:01:45,560
why…

11
00:01:46,080 --> 00:01:48,160
whenever we talk about change,

12
00:01:48,800 --> 00:01:53,400
adults always say that change takes time?

13
00:01:54,720 --> 00:01:55,760
How many years?

14
00:01:55,840 --> 00:01:56,920
Three years?

15
00:01:57,440 --> 00:01:58,480
Five years?

16
00:01:58,560 --> 00:02:02,320
Sometimes, I'm no longer sure

17
00:02:02,880 --> 00:02:04,640
whether it's a real reason

18
00:02:05,200 --> 00:02:07,400
or just an excuse to do nothing at all.

19
00:02:09,560 --> 00:02:10,600
Yes!

20
00:02:10,680 --> 00:02:11,720
- You're right.
- Yes!

21
00:02:11,800 --> 00:02:14,920
I'm not saying that change is easy.

22
00:02:16,160 --> 00:02:17,640
But my point is

23
00:02:18,560 --> 00:02:20,600
that if we start
by doing just one thing at a time,

24
00:02:21,560 --> 00:02:24,240
we'll only see one result at a time.

25
00:02:26,200 --> 00:02:28,760
But if we start
by doing 100 things at once,

26
00:02:30,680 --> 00:02:33,040
the progress of 100 years

27
00:02:33,560 --> 00:02:36,120
might happen within a single year.

28
00:02:36,640 --> 00:02:37,480
Right?

29
00:02:37,560 --> 00:02:38,560
Right!

30
00:02:45,200 --> 00:02:49,440
Paradorn.

31
00:02:49,520 --> 00:02:54,120
Paradorn.

32
00:03:05,160 --> 00:03:06,720
Hello.

33
00:03:06,800 --> 00:03:08,400
I'm Nanno, Number 2,

34
00:03:11,120 --> 00:03:13,240
here with a policy…

35
00:03:16,600 --> 00:03:18,600
What policy should I go with?

36
00:03:20,360 --> 00:03:21,280
Oh.

37
00:03:21,800 --> 00:03:24,040
"New student, new life," then.

38
00:03:25,040 --> 00:03:28,560
Anyway, please take care of me,

39
00:03:29,600 --> 00:03:31,560
and my heart too.

40
00:03:35,280 --> 00:03:37,280
I just applied recently,

41
00:03:37,800 --> 00:03:40,120
so I didn't really prepare any policies.

42
00:03:40,200 --> 00:03:41,960
But that's okay, right?

43
00:03:42,480 --> 00:03:44,240
I'd rather hear ideas from everyone.

44
00:03:52,040 --> 00:03:55,000
Did she copy our idea?
She just changed the wording.

45
00:03:55,080 --> 00:03:57,440
I'm ready to kiss everyone now.

46
00:04:17,280 --> 00:04:18,240
Hey!

47
00:04:18,320 --> 00:04:20,400
- Me first!
- Me first!

48
00:04:20,480 --> 00:04:21,920
Hurry up.

49
00:04:22,000 --> 00:04:24,400
Go, go. Hurry.

50
00:04:24,480 --> 00:04:26,600
The line is long now.

51
00:04:28,120 --> 00:04:30,320
Wow.

52
00:04:49,240 --> 00:04:51,880
I'm Nanno, No. 2. Please support me.

53
00:04:52,600 --> 00:04:53,440
Sure.

54
00:05:02,720 --> 00:05:04,760
I really like your idea.

55
00:05:10,240 --> 00:05:11,960
So I'd like to…

56
00:05:17,840 --> 00:05:19,320
share some ideas too.

57
00:05:21,520 --> 00:05:23,120
If it's you,

58
00:05:23,640 --> 00:05:25,480
I can give you two kisses.

59
00:05:28,440 --> 00:05:29,440
No need.

60
00:05:31,000 --> 00:05:34,720
I'm here to exchange ideas
for the benefit of the school,

61
00:05:35,480 --> 00:05:37,320
not for personal gain.

62
00:05:56,520 --> 00:06:00,360
Hmm… whose is this?
Looks familiar, doesn't it?

63
00:06:00,440 --> 00:06:06,240
- Whoa.
- Boo!

64
00:06:06,320 --> 00:06:07,440
Just throw it away.

65
00:06:15,160 --> 00:06:17,720
Distribute the budget to each class rep

66
00:06:17,800 --> 00:06:19,760
and let them manage it

67
00:06:19,840 --> 00:06:21,480
and set their own rules.

68
00:06:21,560 --> 00:06:24,320
Do they think
everyone has that much free time?

69
00:06:24,840 --> 00:06:26,480
No. No one's free.

70
00:06:26,560 --> 00:06:29,800
Why give class reps more work?

71
00:06:29,880 --> 00:06:32,520
- Yeah, that's true.
- Why?

72
00:06:34,040 --> 00:06:35,760
Yeah!

73
00:06:59,840 --> 00:07:01,680
The latest poll results are out.

74
00:07:01,760 --> 00:07:02,600
Really?

75
00:07:04,520 --> 00:07:05,400
How is it?

76
00:07:06,280 --> 00:07:09,000
Can our 100 policies compete
with Nanno's single kiss?

77
00:07:13,040 --> 00:07:16,200
Honestly, Nanno's initial momentum
was very concerning.

78
00:07:16,280 --> 00:07:18,320
But based on the current poll,
it's clear that

79
00:07:18,400 --> 00:07:21,680
even though she created buzz,
it doesn't mean people will vote for her.

80
00:07:21,760 --> 00:07:23,840
Because most people can still tell

81
00:07:23,920 --> 00:07:26,280
who's real
and who's just chasing attention.

82
00:07:27,000 --> 00:07:27,960
Right?

83
00:07:28,040 --> 00:07:29,920
And from further surveys,

84
00:07:30,000 --> 00:07:33,560
people are interested in the policy
of decentralizing power to class reps.

85
00:07:33,640 --> 00:07:36,760
If we can push this
as our flagship policy,

86
00:07:36,840 --> 00:07:39,200
we'll gain more support from voters.

87
00:07:40,280 --> 00:07:42,040
As for Nanno,

88
00:07:42,880 --> 00:07:46,760
just let her bury herself
with her past scandals.

89
00:07:49,640 --> 00:07:50,600
- Shit.
- Shit.

90
00:07:50,680 --> 00:07:52,880
- Is that real?
- Is that Nanno?

91
00:07:52,960 --> 00:07:54,880
- Who uploaded this?
- Zoom in.

92
00:07:55,480 --> 00:07:56,480
It's so clear.

93
00:07:57,680 --> 00:07:59,880
Nanno's popularity
is definitely going to drop.

94
00:07:59,960 --> 00:08:00,840
Easy for us.

95
00:08:01,360 --> 00:08:03,800
Damn, look at this.

96
00:08:03,880 --> 00:08:05,600
Did she really do it?

97
00:08:05,680 --> 00:08:07,320
Shit.

98
00:08:07,400 --> 00:08:09,360
- Did you see it?
- Student body president?

99
00:08:10,080 --> 00:08:11,440
Did you see your friend yet?

100
00:08:11,520 --> 00:08:12,640
Where?

101
00:08:26,560 --> 00:08:28,400
- Shit, how is this possible?
- Damn.

102
00:08:28,480 --> 00:08:31,520
- Whoa. Shit.
- What?

103
00:08:31,600 --> 00:08:34,320
- Shit. Is that real?
- Damn.

104
00:08:51,120 --> 00:08:54,400
Regarding the controversy about me…

105
00:09:00,360 --> 00:09:02,240
I'd like to confirm

106
00:09:02,840 --> 00:09:04,600
that everything you've seen

107
00:09:06,400 --> 00:09:07,280
is true.

108
00:09:07,360 --> 00:09:09,000
- What?
- Shit.

109
00:09:09,080 --> 00:09:10,800
Damn.

110
00:09:10,880 --> 00:09:13,160
Is that real? Shit.

111
00:09:13,240 --> 00:09:14,120
Gosh.

112
00:09:19,080 --> 00:09:20,600
Just kidding.

113
00:09:35,680 --> 00:09:39,800
These days, anyone can easily fall victim
to something like this.

114
00:09:43,120 --> 00:09:43,960
Shit.

115
00:09:44,960 --> 00:09:46,400
Hey, isn't that a campaign group?

116
00:09:47,360 --> 00:09:48,280
Are they friends?

117
00:09:48,360 --> 00:09:49,560
Yeah, right?

118
00:09:49,640 --> 00:09:50,840
Paradorn, right?

119
00:09:50,920 --> 00:09:52,360
- Paradorn?
- Yeah.

120
00:09:53,080 --> 00:09:54,960
No matter how real it looks,

121
00:09:56,120 --> 00:09:57,680
fake…

122
00:09:58,480 --> 00:09:59,680
is still fake.

123
00:10:03,040 --> 00:10:05,120
And the one who should be punished

124
00:10:05,200 --> 00:10:09,600
is the person who created the fake content
and used it to ruin someone else's life.

125
00:10:10,440 --> 00:10:12,440
Let me give you a hint.

126
00:10:12,960 --> 00:10:14,840
The one who benefits from this

127
00:10:16,280 --> 00:10:17,920
is the one who did it.

128
00:10:21,600 --> 00:10:23,520
- That's playing dirty.
- Yeah.

129
00:10:23,600 --> 00:10:26,720
- Yes.
- That's right!

130
00:10:28,280 --> 00:10:30,920
- Playing dirty.
- Yes!

131
00:10:31,000 --> 00:10:32,240
Yes.

132
00:10:32,320 --> 00:10:33,760
How is that even possible?

133
00:10:34,280 --> 00:10:35,760
She just acts slutty all day.

134
00:10:35,840 --> 00:10:38,440
The real issue is
that people misunderstood

135
00:10:38,520 --> 00:10:40,120
and think we did something dirty

136
00:10:40,200 --> 00:10:43,520
to damage her reputation,
so she's gaining sympathy votes.

137
00:10:43,600 --> 00:10:46,040
On election day,
we have to vote for Nanno.

138
00:10:46,120 --> 00:10:47,000
Yeah!

139
00:10:47,080 --> 00:10:49,120
So we can stand against patriarchy.

140
00:10:49,200 --> 00:10:53,240
Nanno! Nanno!

141
00:10:53,320 --> 00:10:54,760
So stupid.

142
00:10:56,960 --> 00:10:58,280
But did we actually do it?

143
00:10:59,680 --> 00:11:00,880
What do you mean?

144
00:11:00,960 --> 00:11:03,280
Nanno! Nanno!

145
00:11:03,360 --> 00:11:05,080
Didn't I already tell you guys?

146
00:11:06,040 --> 00:11:08,960
The clip was already uploaded.
I just shared it.

147
00:11:09,040 --> 00:11:14,400
Nanno! Nanno!

148
00:11:14,480 --> 00:11:17,160
But you were the first one
who saw it, right?

149
00:11:17,240 --> 00:11:19,800
Why would I go out of my way
to sabotage her?

150
00:11:21,360 --> 00:11:23,680
We're already leading in the polls.
You saw that yourself.

151
00:11:24,200 --> 00:11:26,120
She's not even on my radar.

152
00:11:26,200 --> 00:11:28,240
Didn't Nanno say it herself?

153
00:11:28,320 --> 00:11:31,520
The one who benefits from this
is the one who released the clip.

154
00:11:32,160 --> 00:11:34,080
You all saw who benefits the most.

155
00:11:34,160 --> 00:11:35,280
Hey!

156
00:11:38,000 --> 00:11:39,800
Stop fighting each other.

157
00:11:41,160 --> 00:11:42,800
Polls are just numbers.

158
00:11:43,400 --> 00:11:44,600
POPULARITY POLL
PARADORN, NANNO

159
00:11:44,680 --> 00:11:47,640
Even if those numbers say we're losing.

160
00:11:47,720 --> 00:11:48,720
Hello.

161
00:11:48,800 --> 00:11:50,280
- Nanno.
- Thank you.

162
00:11:50,360 --> 00:11:53,240
Then we have to come up with more policies
and finish them tonight,

163
00:11:53,320 --> 00:11:55,680
so we can continue the campaign tomorrow.

164
00:11:55,760 --> 00:11:57,800
We have hundreds of policies.
What else do you want?

165
00:11:57,880 --> 00:12:00,280
Even if it's thousands,
you still have to think of something.

166
00:12:00,360 --> 00:12:02,080
Whether it works or not, who cares.

167
00:12:02,160 --> 00:12:05,800
Hey. If that's the case, Paradorn won't be
different from the previous president,

168
00:12:06,400 --> 00:12:08,400
making promises he can't keep.

169
00:12:15,080 --> 00:12:17,640
- Please vote for Nanno.
- Number 2.

170
00:12:17,720 --> 00:12:19,920
- Nanno! Nanno!
- Please support Number 2, Nanno.

171
00:12:20,000 --> 00:12:21,360
Please vote for Number 2.

172
00:12:21,440 --> 00:12:23,760
- Vote for Number 2.
- Don't forget to vote for Nanno.

173
00:12:23,840 --> 00:12:27,680
Nanno! Nanno!

174
00:12:28,520 --> 00:12:29,480
Hey!

175
00:12:41,080 --> 00:12:42,080
You know,

176
00:12:43,680 --> 00:12:45,640
I've been preparing since last year

177
00:12:46,160 --> 00:12:48,000
for this year's
student body president election.

178
00:12:49,280 --> 00:12:51,600
I've been brainstorming policies
with the team nonstop.

179
00:12:51,680 --> 00:12:52,840
But you…

180
00:12:55,680 --> 00:12:57,880
You didn't even seem prepared at all.

181
00:13:01,560 --> 00:13:05,040
And look at you now.
You're even more popular than me.

182
00:13:06,280 --> 00:13:07,520
How did you do it?

183
00:13:08,880 --> 00:13:10,000
Yeah.

184
00:13:10,520 --> 00:13:11,960
How do you think?

185
00:13:19,400 --> 00:13:20,800
I misunderstood.

186
00:13:22,440 --> 00:13:26,800
I thought people would choose a leader
based on reason and facts.

187
00:13:28,480 --> 00:13:30,280
But in reality, that's not the case.

188
00:13:31,320 --> 00:13:34,120
You're really serious
about this election, aren't you?

189
00:13:36,440 --> 00:13:37,960
Because this is my first step.

190
00:13:39,720 --> 00:13:42,640
The first step to changing something.

191
00:13:43,600 --> 00:13:45,200
Starting from this school,

192
00:13:46,720 --> 00:13:48,960
so that in the future,

193
00:13:49,600 --> 00:13:52,840
I might have a chance
to change society for the better.

194
00:13:54,600 --> 00:13:56,240
Better how?

195
00:13:58,160 --> 00:14:00,200
The way you want it to be?

196
00:14:08,480 --> 00:14:10,800
But there are still three days left.

197
00:14:10,880 --> 00:14:12,840
Anything can happen, right?

198
00:14:23,760 --> 00:14:24,640
Hey!

199
00:14:32,480 --> 00:14:33,720
Shit.

200
00:14:33,800 --> 00:14:35,080
Oh.

201
00:14:35,760 --> 00:14:36,720
Hey.

202
00:14:36,800 --> 00:14:39,000
- Does it hurt?
- Oh.

203
00:14:39,520 --> 00:14:40,760
That's bad.

204
00:14:41,280 --> 00:14:43,360
SUPERHERO!

205
00:14:44,280 --> 00:14:45,480
Please don't get up yet.

206
00:14:46,000 --> 00:14:48,760
Easy.

207
00:14:48,840 --> 00:14:50,320
I THOUGHT HE WAS SUPERMAN

208
00:14:50,400 --> 00:14:52,760
Are you okay? Take it easy.

209
00:14:52,840 --> 00:14:53,680
Is he okay?

210
00:14:53,760 --> 00:14:54,720
Are you all right?

211
00:14:55,680 --> 00:14:57,560
Damn, that was so cool.

212
00:14:58,360 --> 00:14:59,240
Are you all right?

213
00:14:59,320 --> 00:15:02,920
Wow, that's straight out
of a Korean drama.

214
00:15:03,000 --> 00:15:04,480
Such a gentleman.

215
00:15:04,560 --> 00:15:06,640
THE REAL HERO

216
00:15:06,720 --> 00:15:08,840
I'LL VOTE FOR HIM

217
00:15:08,920 --> 00:15:09,840
NO NEED FOR AN ELECTION. CROWN HIM.

218
00:15:09,920 --> 00:15:10,960
WE NEED SMART CROSSWALK PROJECT!

219
00:15:11,040 --> 00:15:12,400
VOTE NUMBER 1

220
00:15:13,360 --> 00:15:16,520
ELECTION DAY

221
00:15:16,600 --> 00:15:18,400
BALLOT FOR THE 66TH STUDENT BODY PRESIDENT

222
00:15:18,480 --> 00:15:19,600
CANDIDATE NUMBER

223
00:15:45,560 --> 00:15:51,120
CONGRATULATIONS TO MR. PARADORN
THE 66TH STUDENT BODY PRESIDENT

224
00:15:57,480 --> 00:15:59,040
Congratulations, Paradorn.

225
00:16:04,360 --> 00:16:05,480
Thanks, Nanno.

226
00:17:05,840 --> 00:17:07,120
<i>Hey, hurry up.</i>

227
00:17:09,520 --> 00:17:12,200
<i>Take these three boxes out</i>
<i>and replace them.</i>

228
00:17:33,600 --> 00:17:34,640
What the hell?

229
00:17:35,400 --> 00:17:36,440
Shit!

230
00:17:38,800 --> 00:17:40,400
What the hell did you do, New?

231
00:17:40,480 --> 00:17:41,600
Do you even realize?!

232
00:17:43,280 --> 00:17:45,040
Damn. I might have already won.

233
00:17:45,120 --> 00:17:46,280
Damn it.

234
00:17:46,360 --> 00:17:47,360
Damn.

235
00:17:47,440 --> 00:17:48,440
Damn you.

236
00:17:48,960 --> 00:17:51,560
You're really working hard
at being an idiot.

237
00:17:58,160 --> 00:17:59,160
I…

238
00:18:00,120 --> 00:18:01,880
Paradorn Tangnaitham,

239
00:18:03,200 --> 00:18:05,120
the 66th student body president,

240
00:18:06,280 --> 00:18:11,040
have discovered that there was fraud
in this election.

241
00:18:12,600 --> 00:18:16,320
The one responsible
is one of my own party members.

242
00:18:42,120 --> 00:18:44,120
I was the one
who replaced all the ballot boxes

243
00:18:45,960 --> 00:18:48,000
to ensure Paradorn's victory.

244
00:18:48,520 --> 00:18:49,360
- What?
- What the fuck?

245
00:18:49,440 --> 00:18:51,400
- Just get out.
- Why would you do that?

246
00:18:51,480 --> 00:18:53,320
- Go home and don't come back.
- Yeah.

247
00:18:53,400 --> 00:18:55,920
- Terrible.
- Get out of here.

248
00:18:56,000 --> 00:18:57,760
- Go away.
- What an asshole.

249
00:18:57,840 --> 00:18:59,720
- Look at him.
- Just go home.

250
00:18:59,800 --> 00:19:01,080
- Asshole.
- It's my vote.

251
00:19:01,160 --> 00:19:02,840
How could you do that?

252
00:19:02,920 --> 00:19:04,240
Why?

253
00:19:12,960 --> 00:19:14,960
To show my sincerity

254
00:19:17,240 --> 00:19:18,720
and take responsibility

255
00:19:19,680 --> 00:19:22,440
for selecting a corrupt team member,

256
00:19:26,000 --> 00:19:29,080
I hereby resign from my position
as student body president,

257
00:19:30,040 --> 00:19:33,240
effective immediately.

258
00:19:40,320 --> 00:19:42,400
What the hell is this?

259
00:19:51,880 --> 00:19:53,800
Why didn't you destroy the evidence?

260
00:19:55,640 --> 00:19:57,640
I didn't make a copy.

261
00:20:00,880 --> 00:20:02,400
Why didn't you expose me yourself?

262
00:20:03,280 --> 00:20:04,560
I just wanted to know

263
00:20:05,080 --> 00:20:08,800
whether you're really a hero or a villain.

264
00:20:13,480 --> 00:20:15,760
Haven't I already proven my innocence?

265
00:20:18,360 --> 00:20:20,120
By getting New expelled?

266
00:20:21,320 --> 00:20:23,360
That so-called "innocence"
is pretty brutal.

267
00:20:29,560 --> 00:20:30,800
I'll tell you something.

268
00:20:33,360 --> 00:20:35,600
Anyone who wants to go into politics

269
00:20:36,120 --> 00:20:38,160
must have a clean record.

270
00:20:38,760 --> 00:20:40,840
You can't afford stains like this.

271
00:20:42,040 --> 00:20:45,360
And besides, those who do wrong
should face the consequences.

272
00:20:46,440 --> 00:20:47,840
Isn't that fair?

273
00:20:49,000 --> 00:20:51,040
And what if you lose

274
00:20:51,920 --> 00:20:53,280
the next election?

275
00:20:56,440 --> 00:20:57,440
Remember this.

276
00:20:58,960 --> 00:21:00,320
People like me

277
00:21:01,400 --> 00:21:03,360
don't make the same mistake twice.

278
00:21:04,600 --> 00:21:08,440
Humans tend to repeat the same mistakes
over and over again

279
00:21:08,520 --> 00:21:12,040
until they die
or until they finally stop being foolish.

280
00:21:12,120 --> 00:21:13,280
That's not me!

281
00:21:15,360 --> 00:21:19,840
But most people die
before they stop being foolish.

282
00:21:21,720 --> 00:21:24,200
What makes you think
you'll be any different?

283
00:21:24,920 --> 00:21:27,280
Because you think
you're better than everyone else?

284
00:21:31,440 --> 00:21:32,680
That's exactly

285
00:21:34,000 --> 00:21:36,080
why I like you, Paradorn.

286
00:21:39,840 --> 00:21:41,520
Shall we find out

287
00:21:42,640 --> 00:21:45,600
what kind of person
you'll become in the future?

288
00:22:26,920 --> 00:22:28,000
HOMECOMING DAY

289
00:22:28,080 --> 00:22:30,640
OUTSTANDING ALUMNUS
MINISTER PARADORN TANGNAITHAM

290
00:22:31,920 --> 00:22:33,960
I would like to thank
the alumni association

291
00:22:34,040 --> 00:22:36,920
for granting me
this outstanding alumni award.

292
00:22:37,800 --> 00:22:39,280
As you all know,

293
00:22:40,120 --> 00:22:43,000
I first ran for election at this school.

294
00:22:43,640 --> 00:22:44,960
But it's more than that.

295
00:22:46,160 --> 00:22:51,760
Everything that made me
who I am today started here.

296
00:23:13,080 --> 00:23:13,920
<i>Hey, hurry up.</i>

297
00:23:15,240 --> 00:23:17,760
<i>Take these three boxes out</i>
<i>and replace them.</i>

298
00:23:19,440 --> 00:23:21,200
<i>Hurry. What are you doing?</i>

299
00:23:23,720 --> 00:23:24,560
<i>If we get caught…</i>

300
00:23:25,960 --> 00:23:27,760
How would you explain this, sir?

301
00:23:27,840 --> 00:23:29,520
Did you rig an election before?

302
00:23:29,600 --> 00:23:30,640
Please answer, sir.

303
00:23:30,720 --> 00:23:31,960
He's so fake.

304
00:23:32,040 --> 00:23:33,360
I shouldn't have believed him.

305
00:23:33,440 --> 00:23:35,400
I'm not voting for you anymore.

306
00:23:35,480 --> 00:23:36,840
- Yeah, me too.
- You asshole.

307
00:23:37,440 --> 00:23:40,000
That's not what happened.
Please listen to me.

308
00:23:40,080 --> 00:23:43,360
Hey, I did my best. I took responsibility.

309
00:23:43,440 --> 00:23:45,600
Please… I already took responsibility.

310
00:23:45,680 --> 00:23:46,880
Hey, listen to me.

311
00:23:46,960 --> 00:23:49,240
I already took responsibility.

312
00:23:49,320 --> 00:23:52,320
- Sir, answer us.
- What really happened?

313
00:23:52,400 --> 00:23:55,880
- That's enough. Excuse us.
- Answer us, sir.

314
00:23:55,960 --> 00:23:58,760
- Excuse us.
- Hey!

315
00:24:18,960 --> 00:24:20,840
Think again.

316
00:24:53,080 --> 00:24:54,360
<i>Hey, hurry up.</i>

317
00:24:54,440 --> 00:24:56,800
<i>Take these three boxes out</i>
<i>and replace them.</i>

318
00:25:16,880 --> 00:25:20,160
Hello, New.
Call everyone for an urgent meeting.

319
00:25:21,320 --> 00:25:26,560
I want us to start working on
the smart crosswalk project immediately.

320
00:25:38,840 --> 00:25:40,760
We finally won, Paradorn.

321
00:25:40,840 --> 00:25:42,160
Damn, this is amazing.

322
00:25:43,040 --> 00:25:44,600
I've been waiting for this day.

323
00:25:45,400 --> 00:25:47,400
ANNUAL POLICY: SMART CROSSWALK PROJECT

324
00:25:48,080 --> 00:25:49,520
Right, Paradorn?

325
00:25:51,360 --> 00:25:52,360
Paradorn.

326
00:25:57,520 --> 00:25:58,520
Hey, Paradorn.

327
00:26:49,920 --> 00:26:51,880
Are you okay?

328
00:27:06,320 --> 00:27:07,320
Nanno!

329
00:27:15,480 --> 00:27:16,480
Nanno!

330
00:27:19,720 --> 00:27:22,840
Tell me the truth. Is what I saw real?

331
00:27:24,840 --> 00:27:26,600
You don't have to believe it.

332
00:27:29,120 --> 00:27:32,280
Then delete that damn clip
right here in front of me.

333
00:27:34,720 --> 00:27:36,880
I said there's no copy.

334
00:27:36,960 --> 00:27:39,560
- So then there's no copy.
- You think I'm stupid?

335
00:27:40,760 --> 00:27:42,720
I don't need a copy.

336
00:27:51,080 --> 00:27:52,880
Because your wrongdoing

337
00:27:54,520 --> 00:27:55,680
goes far beyond that.

338
00:27:55,760 --> 00:27:58,480
<i>Hey. I almost really got hit</i>
<i>by the car earlier.</i>

339
00:27:58,560 --> 00:28:00,520
<i>You should pay me more.</i>

340
00:28:00,600 --> 00:28:02,480
<i>We agreed on the price.</i>
<i>That's all you get.</i>

341
00:28:02,560 --> 00:28:04,080
<i>Why are you asking for more now?</i>

342
00:28:04,160 --> 00:28:07,040
That accident where you became a hero

343
00:28:08,120 --> 00:28:10,640
was your doing too, wasn't it?

344
00:28:14,200 --> 00:28:15,960
Like I said,

345
00:28:16,040 --> 00:28:21,560
people keep making
the same stupid mistakes until they die.

346
00:29:16,120 --> 00:29:17,720
<i>Some people,</i>

347
00:29:18,240 --> 00:29:20,240
<i>even when they stand in the light,</i>

348
00:29:20,760 --> 00:29:22,800
<i>let darkness consume them.</i>

349
00:29:26,960 --> 00:29:28,680
<i>But others,</i>

350
00:29:29,240 --> 00:29:31,080
<i>even when surrounded by darkness,</i>

351
00:29:32,120 --> 00:29:35,360
<i>refuse to let</i>
<i>their inner light be extinguished.</i>

352
00:29:48,160 --> 00:29:49,280
Hey!

353
00:29:54,840 --> 00:29:55,960
Nanno.

354
00:30:03,920 --> 00:30:05,360
How did you get here?

355
00:30:08,640 --> 00:30:10,320
Shouldn't I be the one asking you?

356
00:32:43,240 --> 00:32:45,360
Honestly, I feel happier right now

357
00:32:45,440 --> 00:32:48,040
than I did
when I was appointed as a minister.

358
00:32:48,560 --> 00:32:50,280
As everyone knows,

359
00:32:50,360 --> 00:32:53,240
I first ran for election at this school.

360
00:32:53,920 --> 00:32:55,120
But it's more than that.

361
00:32:55,640 --> 00:33:01,080
Everything that made me
who I am today started here.

362
00:33:01,160 --> 00:33:03,360
HOMECOMING DAY
OUTSTANDING ALUMNUS

363
00:33:42,640 --> 00:33:44,880
<i>A world that has been reset…</i>

364
00:33:45,800 --> 00:33:50,680
<i>I hope</i>
<i>there are still some good people left.</i>

365
00:33:54,560 --> 00:33:58,160
<i>See you again next semester, everyone.</i>

366
00:36:02,160 --> 00:36:07,160
Subtitle translation by: Panuwat Baikeawon
